</OrgName>
<Desc><entry>A community service arising out of the deaths and knife attacks which occurred in Pitsmoor and Burngreave.  The Street Pastoring and mentoring scheme is a response to gang culture, anti-social behaviour and alcohol and drug misuse.  Aims to get to know people, build relationships and find out about the needs of the people on the streets through listening, caring and helping.  Works in teams of 3 or 4 people on Friday and Saturday nights 10pm-4am, patrolling streets and visiting night clubs.  Christian volunteers are needed.</entry>
</Desc>
